CONTEXT GuardedMaintenance IN ENGLISH
-- Negative test: functional maintenance whose deleter carries a guard (the
-- SIAM `sessionPersonRef` pattern). `determine` keeps `sRef ⊇ sAccount;aRef`;
-- `clear` removes an `sRef` pair only where the session is a user AND the pair
-- is no longer derivable (`isUser;sRef |- sAccount;aRef`). The deleter's
-- antecedent mentions `sRef`, but its *allowed region* is still `sAccount;aRef`,
-- so it only ever removes pairs outside that definition — the guard is
-- irrelevant to convergence. This MUST stay silent (§6.5 refinement b), and it
-- checks that the certificate tolerates a composition-guarded deleter.

RELATION sAccount[Session*Account] [UNI]
RELATION aRef[Account*Ref] [UNI]
RELATION sRef[Session*Ref] [UNI]
RELATION isUser[Session*Session] [PROP]

ROLE ExecEngine MAINTAINS "determine sRef"
RULE "determine sRef" : sAccount;aRef |- sRef
VIOLATION ( TXT "{EX} InsPair;sRef;Session;", SRC I, TXT ";Ref;", TGT I )

ROLE ExecEngine MAINTAINS "clear sRef"
RULE "clear sRef" : isUser;sRef |- sAccount;aRef
VIOLATION ( TXT "{EX} DelPair;sRef;Session;", SRC I, TXT ";Ref;", TGT I )

ENDCONTEXT
